race.comment: ANXO (3) didn't measure up in town last time out but should find this assignment much more to his liking. Last outing at this course the start prior returned a second over 1100m. Likely to play a major role in the finish. Former Victorian TORONESS (10) is having her start for the new yard but should appreciate the drop back in company here. Top-three aspirations. LAAN (5) is facing the starter for the first time but won't need to be a superstar to be competitive against this lot. Keep safe from the Gollan camp. The well-related RARE MOON (11) (half to G3 winner Icarian Dream) best of the rest.
